  "body": "Instead of:\n\n``` console\n$ kubectl get events\nFIRSTSEEN                         LASTSEEN                          COUNT     NAME          KIND      SUBOBJECT   REASON             SOURCE         MESSAGE\nTue, 21 Jul 2015 16:25:06 -0700   Wed, 05 Aug 2015 08:56:09 -0700   416805    frontend4     Pod                   failedScheduling   {scheduler }   Failed for reason MatchNodeSelector and possibly others\n```\n\nlet's print\n\n``` console\n$ kubectl get events\nFIRSTSEEN        LASTSEEN         COUNT     NAME          KIND      SUBOBJECT   REASON             SOURCE         MESSAGE\n15 days ago      30 seconds ago   416805    frontend4     Pod                   failedScheduling   {scheduler }   Failed for reason MatchNodeSelector and possibly others\n```\n\nThat save about 30 characters of width.  We could have a flag like `--machine-readable-time` or something to enable the old behavior.  Default to the new.\n\nWe could use https://gowalker.org/github.com/dustin/go-humanize or just write a 20 line function that specifically handles humanized time printing.\n",
